records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody on WRIT.
NO CONTEST plea entered to count 1, deliver heroin-2nd or subsequent offense.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 2 and 3.  Motion granted.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of thirty-eight (38) months.  That is fourteen (14) months initial confinement followed by twenty-four(24) months extended supervision, consecutive to the sentence presently being served on case no: 09 CF 54.
The Court finds the defendant eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) continue with his AODA treatment;
2) obtain and maintain stable and verifiable employment;
3) defendant is not to have more than $100.00 on his person at any time without the agent's permission;
4) obtain and maintain a stable residence;
5) maintain health counseling as recommended;
6) comply with any prescription medication and do not give any medication to anyone;
7) no contact with Kimberly Sinase, Amanda Adelman or James Schacht;
8) no contact with any know drug users;
9) pay court costs including $300.00 buy money to the Metro Drug Unit;
10) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
11) submit to DNA sample.
Minutes.
